{
  "id": "L8S",
  "title": "Discussing Your Daily Routine",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Let's learn how to talk about your 'rutina diaria' (daily routine). We will start with the morning."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V01",
      "data": {
        "La rutina": "The routine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Normalmente",
        "meaning": "Usually"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo me despierto",
        "meaning": "I wake up"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "A las...",
        "meaning": "At... (for time, e.g., 'at seven')"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V02",
      "data": {
        "Siete": "Seven"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L8S_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Ocho",
        "phonetic": "[ˈo.tʃo]",
        "tip": "The 'ch' sound in Spanish is just like the 'ch' in the English word 'cheese'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V03",
      "data": {
        "Ocho": "Eight"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo desayuno",
        "meaning": "I have breakfast"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V04",
      "data": {
        "Café": "Coffee"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V05",
      "data": {
        "Tostadas": "Toast"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo voy",
        "meaning": "I go"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Al trabajo",
        "meaning": "To work"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V06",
      "data": {
        "En bicicleta": "By bike"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V07",
      "data": {
        "En tren": "By train"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L8S_S01",
      "title": "Your Morning",
      "setting": "Your friend, Sofía, asks about your morning routine.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "State what time you wake up",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Hola! Hablemos de la rutina. Normalmente, ¿a qué hora te despiertas?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say what you have for breakfast",
          "chatbot_message": "Interesante. ¿Y qué desayunas?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Explain how you go to work",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Qué rico! Y después, ¿cómo vas al trabajo?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great! Now let's talk about your work or study day. We'll learn verbs like 'empezar' (to start) and 'terminar' (to finish)."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo empiezo",
        "meaning": "I start"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "A trabajar",
        "meaning": "To work"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V08",
      "data": {
        "Nueve": "Nine"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo almuerzo",
        "meaning": "I have lunch"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "To say 'one o'clock', you use 'a la una'. For all other hours, you use 'a las...', for example, 'a las dos'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V09",
      "data": {
        "A la una": "At one o'clock"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V10",
      "data": {
        "A las dos": "At two o'clock"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo termino",
        "meaning": "I finish"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V11",
      "data": {
        "Cinco": "Five"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L8S_S02",
      "title": "Your Afternoon",
      "setting": "Sofía continues the conversation, asking about your afternoon.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "State what time you start work",
          "chatbot_message": "¡En bicicleta! Muy bien. ¿Y a qué hora empiezas a trabajar?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say when you have lunch",
          "chatbot_message": "Entendido. ¿Y cuándo almuerzas?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Mention when you finish work",
          "chatbot_message": "Bien. ¿A qué hora terminas de trabajar?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Last part! Let's talk about your evening and learn how to ask questions back to keep the conversation going."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Después del trabajo",
        "meaning": "After work"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo cocino",
        "meaning": "I cook"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E13",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo hago deporte",
        "meaning": "I do sports"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L8S_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "Veo",
        "phonetic": "[ˈbe.o]",
        "tip": "The 'v' in Spanish often sounds like a soft 'b'. Try to say 'beo'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E14",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo veo la tele",
        "meaning": "I watch TV"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E15",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Yo ceno",
        "meaning": "I have dinner"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L8S_V12",
      "data": {
        "Las ocho": "Eight o'clock"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L8S_E16",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "¿Y tú?",
        "meaning": "And you?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L8S_S03",
      "title": "Your Evening",
      "setting": "You're now ready to describe your evening and ask Sofía about her routine.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Describe an after-work activity",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Perfecto! ¿Qué haces normalmente después del trabajo?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say what time you have dinner",
          "chatbot_message": "¡Qué bien! A mí también me gusta cocinar. ¿A qué hora cenas?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask about her routine",
          "chatbot_message": "A las ocho. Mi rutina es muy similar."
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}